## 3. Methodology

The audit was conducted using the following tools and techniques:

### Tools

| Tool | Type | Purpose |
|------|------|---------|
| **Slither** | Static Analysis | Taint tracking, data flow analysis, detector rules |
| **Mythril** | Symbolic Execution | Path exploration, constraint solving |
| **Echidna** | Fuzz Testing | Property-based fuzzing, invariant testing |
| **Foundry Forge** | Compilation | Build verification, artifact generation |
| **AI Classifier** | ML Classification | TP/FP/TN/FN classification, severity reassessment |
| **Exploit Engine** | Dynamic Testing | On-chain exploit verification via Anvil fork |

### Process

1. **Source Acquisition** — Fetch verified source code from GitHub / Sourcify / Etherscan
2. **Compilation** — Build with matching Solidity compiler version via solc-select
3. **Static Analysis** — Run Slither with appropriate configuration tier
4. **Symbolic Analysis** — Execute Mythril with RPC endpoint for state exploration
5. **Fuzz Testing** — Run Echidna with auto-generated property tests
6. **AI Analysis** — Classify findings, reassess severity, generate fix recommendations
7. **Exploit Verification** — Test TP critical/high findings on forked mainnet state
8. **Report Generation** — Compile findings into Immunefi and full audit reports

